p:
Two bees start at the same spot and fly at different rates in the following modified directions. Bee $A$ travels $1$ foot north, then $1$ foot east, then $2$ feet upwards, and then continues to repeat this pattern. Bee $B$ travels $1$ foot south, then $1.5$ feet west, and then continues to repeat this pattern. In what directions are the bees traveling when they are exactly $15$ feet away from each other?
$\textbf{(A) } A\ \text{east, } B\ \text{west}   \qquad \textbf{(B) } A\ \text{north, } B\ \text{south}
\qquad \textbf{(C) } A\ \text{north, } B\ \text{west} \qquad \textbf{(D) } A\ \text{up, } B\ \text{south}
\qquad \textbf{(E) } A\ \text{up, } B\ \text{west}$
